1. if you don't have it yet, install composer
2. install dependencies with composer ```php composer install ```
3. create an account on https://getstream.io
4. generate the config file php artisan vendor:publish --provider="GetStream\StreamLaravel\StreamLaravelServiceProvider"
5. get your API credentials (key and secret) from https://getstream.io 
6. put your credentials in the config file created by artisan (stream-laravel)
7. adjust your database settings in config/database.php
8. run database setup ``` ./provision.sh ```

The example app is based on stream-laravel package, please refer to its documentation: https://github.com/GetStream/Stream-Laravel

If you have any problems please open a issue on github and paste any error you get in the console.
